FBIS4-14135 "drnes082_r_94003" FBIS-NES-94-082 Daily Report 27 Apr 1994 India Legislators Support Increased Defense Spending Legislators Support Increased Defense Spending BK2804014294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 27 Apr 94 BK2804014294 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] Members participating in the resumed discussion on the working of the Defense Ministry in the Rajya Sabha today called for increased allocation for defense research and modernization of the armed forces. They complimented the defense scientists for the breakthrough achieved in indigenous missile technology. Members asked the government not to succumb to any pressure and slow down the pace of self-reliance in this field. Members from both sides welcomed the improved ties with China and some of them suggested that India should go in for joint defense ventures with China and Iran.
